title: pkg_resources.DistributionNotFound: The 'websockets==7.*' distribution was not found and is required by uvicorn
body:
**Describe the bug**
After a plain installation on mac, I get the following error log
```

pkg_resources.ContextualVersionConflict: (websockets 8.0.1 (/Users/amustapha/ludwig/lib/python3.7/site-packages/websockets-8.0.1-py3.7-macosx-10.14-x86_64.egg), Requirement.parse('websockets==7.*'), {'uvicorn'})

During handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:

  File "/Users/amustapha/ludwig/lib/python3.7/site-packages/setuptools-39.1.0-py3.7.egg/pkg_resources/__init__.py", line 589, in _build_from_requirements
  File "/Users/amustapha/ludwig/lib/python3.7/site-packages/setuptools-39.1.0-py3.7.egg/pkg_resources/__init__.py", line 778, in resolve
pkg_resources.DistributionNotFound: The 'websockets==7.*' distribution was not found and is required by uvicorn
```

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:

1. Fresh install on MacBook Pro
2. run `ludwig -m ludwig.train --data_train_csv R_75.csv --mdf model_definition.yaml`
